# steam package вЂ” local env template
#
# Copy this file to ``.env`` and fill in the values below.  ``.env`` is
# gitignored (see ``.gitignore``) вЂ” never commit real credentials.

# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ STEAM_API_KEY в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# Personal Steam Web API key.  Needed to regenerate the VCR fixtures
# under ``vcr/`` (``webapi.yaml`` in particular вЂ” its ``ISteamUser``
# and ``ISteamWebAPIUtil.GetSupportedAPIList`` calls require an
# authenticated key).  NOT needed for normal ``poetry run pytest``
# because the checked-in cassettes replay in playback-only mode
# (``RecordMode.NONE``).
#
# How to get one:
#   1. Sign in at https://steamcommunity.com/dev/apikey with a real
#      Steam account (must have Steam Guard + phone verified вЂ” Valve
#      restricts API-key issuance to accounts that have made at least
#      one purchase and enabled 2FA).
#   2. Enter a domain name (``localhost`` works вЂ” Valve doesn't verify
#      the domain).
#   3. Copy the 32-hex-character key from the confirmation page.
#
# Key format: 32 uppercase hex characters (no dashes).
#   e.g.  ABCD1234...     вЂ” 32 chars total
#
# Once set, follow the regen recipe in the "Regenerating VCR cassettes"
# section of the README (or the git commit that introduced this file)
# to refresh ``vcr/webapi.yaml``.
STEAM_API_KEY=
